## Engineering Standards

**Before writing any Go code**, always read:
```
.claude/skills/golang-skills/SKILL.md
```

Then load the relevant sub-skills for the task at hand (see routing table in SKILL.md).

## Architecture

**Pattern**: Hexagonal Architecture (Ports & Adapters)
**Domain**: [domain name] — entities: [list key entities]
**Layer structure**:
```
internal/
├── domain/        → pure business logic, zero external imports
├── app/           → use cases / command+query handlers
├── adapters/      → HTTP, gRPC, Postgres, Redis, Kafka implementations
└── ports/         → secondary port interfaces (notifier, publisher)
```

